# config/generation.toml declares line_endings = "lf" as the single
# authoritative policy for every committed generated schema: `generate`
# always writes LF, so a byte-for-byte drift check only ever passes if
# the committed bytes stay LF too. Without this file, a Windows Git
# client's default core.autocrlf behavior converts the committed LF
# bytes to CRLF on checkout, and `generate --check` then reports drift
# against content that was never actually regenerated -- purely a
# checkout-time conversion, not a real difference (observed live in
# cross-platform-mage.yml run 30075727901 on windows-latest: every
# committed schema under schemas/ reported as drifted).
schemas/** text eol=lf
